<h3>We use cookies to:</h3>
<ul class="ml-5">
	<li>1.	Remember certain information about users so you don’t have to give the same information again;</li>
	<li>2.	Understand how people use our Site so we can improve the way information is provided. This information is not Personal Information and is used to track trends and behaviours, gathering data such as date and time of visits, pages viewed, time spent at the Site, and the site visited just before and just after the organisaiton’s site;</li>
	<li>3.	From time to time, display advertisements based on parts of the Site you have visited or interacted with;</li>
	<li>4.	Prevent fraudulent activity;</li>
	<li>5.	Improve security.</li>
	<li>6.	You agree to our use of cookies by continuing to use our websites</li>
</ul>
<p>To browse anonymously, you may set your browser to disable cookies or delete cookies. Disabling cookies for some services will impact your ability to use that service. Users may choose not to accept cookies. Your web browser may alert and permit you to refuse cookies. When you receive an alert, you may choose at that time to refuse that cookie. If the use of cookies is a concern to you, then please make sure your browser has this capability, and that you set your browser to alert you accordingly.</p>
<p>However, some product features and services provided by Himmat require you to accept cookies in order to be able to use the particular functionality or service. These cookies are used to establish a link between the user and the application server. The cookies contain unique session IDs, and no user data is stored on the cookies.</p>

